Under the legitimation principle, the person responsible within the Personal Data Protection Authority may only process personal data when the owner &nbsp;grants his consent for one or more specific purposes, when necessary for the fulfilment of a court order, for the defence or recognition of the rights of the holder/owner before a public authority, to protect the vital interests of the holder/owner or of another natural person; among other legitimate and informed reasons.Last modified 24 Jan 2022
				
			